Job description
Emulation and Prototyping has become critical & indispensable part of SoC designs verification with growing design size and complexity. Shift Left on overall validation of the functional and performance intent of the ASIC/SoC/Chip DUT in a system level involving Application SW, drivers/SDK, Operating Systems of interest, Industry standard test/traffic/Exerciser & debug tools is the focus of Verification Solutions Product Engineering group. As a core part of this focus, we develop innovative solutions around Virtual transactors, third-party and/or customer specific test infrastructure.

Looking for a Product Engineer to be part of Virtual Solutions Product Engineering Team to help drive PCIe, CXL VSA product deployments, working in close collaboration with customers, development & Product validation teams, leading to successful deployment of overall solution.

Roles and Responsibilities:
• Supporting the Synopsys Virtual System Adaptors for PCIe, CXL products
• Responsible for debugging the protocol PCIe , CXL issues at RTL and system level.
• Bring up of PCIe, CXL Virtual Host and Device Solutions on customer designs as needed working with AE teams.
• Creating use cases / prototype designs based on customer needs and showcase the feasibility of solutions.
• Track and debug customer issues and work with R&D team on issue resolution.
• Managing the existing requests, assign appropriate priorities to bug fixes and new feature developments.
• Managing the release process to ensure that the product is released on time and contains the enhancements that were planned.
Requirements:
• MS with 8+ or BS with 10+ Years of experience in Simulation, Emulation, Prototyping or ASIC design/verification.
• Knowledge of key protocol’s like PCIe, CXL, NVMe
• Strong trouble shooting and problem-solving skills;
• Experience in SoC design porting on emulators and/or prototyping solution, creating FPGA friendly interfaces, adoption of testbench environment and prototyping SoC environment w/ debug is highly preferred.
• Domain knowledge in one or more areas: Networking, Storage, Automotive.
• Working knowledge of C/C++/System C is a plus
• Excellent customer interface, communication, and planning skills
